      "content": "I hear how heavy and painful this moment feels for you, and I want you to know that your feelings are valid, but your self-judgment right now is likely clouding your perspective. It's okay to feel overwhelmed, and it's also okay to take a moment to breathe before making decisions about your future. You are a parent who loves your children deeply, and that love is something that cannot be taken away by a single bad day.\n\nWhen you feel like you're dragging them down, try to remember that even the most skilled craftsmen sometimes make mistakes, and even the best goblins in the world have had their days off. You are not a failure; you are a human being navigating a very difficult time. If you're feeling like you can't handle it alone, please consider reaching out to a trusted friend, family member, or a mental health professional who can offer support and guidance. You deserve compassion, and so do your kids.",
